#N canvas 632 124 509 497 10;
#X msg 17 54 1;
#X text 17 24 You can write wherever you want by inserting a COMMENT.
;
#X text 54 49 A MESSAGE BOX has a flag shape and sends its contents
when activated by another message or a click.;
#X floatatom 35 147 5 0 0 0 - - -;
#X text 84 138 A NUMBER BOX has a punched-card shape. It holds and
displays a number that can change.;
#X text 17 6 MY FIRST PATCH;
#X msg 86 254 2;
#X obj 35 104 + 1;
#X floatatom 16 429 5 0 0 0 - - -;
#X text 82 98 An OBJECT BOX has a rectangular shape and hold objects
that do things with signals \, messages and numbers.;
#X text 32 176 Wires (or cables) connect the boxes. An object will
only update its output when it "receives" an input. You have to go
to EXECUTE MODE and click the MESSAGE BOX so it can "send" its contents
to the OBJECT BOX which will then send its output to the NUMBER BOX.
;
#X obj 16 263 + 3;
#X text 37 285 An OBJECT BOX can take more than one input. When it
does \, it will process them always from right to left and will produce
an output only when the left-most input is received. If the OBJECT
BOX already has a (default) argument \, in this case '3' \, the second
input will take the place of the argument given in the OBJECT BOX.
If you clicked the MESSAGE BOX with '1' before clicking the MESSAGE
BOX with '2' \, The NUMBER BOX will show '4' until you click the MESSAGE
BOX with '2' and then the one with '1' again.;
#X connect 0 0 7 0;
#X connect 0 0 11 0;
#X connect 6 0 11 1;
#X connect 7 0 3 0;
#X connect 11 0 8 0;
